	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64346613"><p>Very future-proof.  Properly cared for, it may be possible to play vinyl centuries from now.  There are already Edison cylinders over 100 years old, and the composition of modern records may be even more stable.  </p><p>The CD-format hasn't changed in decades, but it's still wrapped up with some fairly advanced technology that's much more easily lost if society breaks down.  CDs have only been subject to simulated aging tests at best, no real world experience with it as a century-long archiving format.</p></div>
	</div>

